<FIRST>r a PM-People--KittyDukakis     07-15 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People--Kitty Dukakis,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kitty Dukakis Injured Slightly in Cape Cop Traffic Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FALMOUTH, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kitty Dukakis was treated for a minor neck
injury and released from a hospital here after the car in which she
was riding was struck in the rear by a pickup truck, authorities
said.
   Mrs. Dukakis, whose sister, Janet Peters, was driving at the time
of the accident, was admitted to Falmouth Hospital about 6:30 p.m.
Friday and released an hour later, nursing supervisor Pauline
Giabbai said. Peters also was treated and released.
   The driver of the pickup truck, John M. Haddad, 22, was cited for
failing to use care in stopping, following too closely and failing
to have his vehicle inspected
   Mrs. Dukakis, 52, completed a 30-day treatment for alcohol
dependency in March. She has been working on a book and speaking on
the lecture circuit since her husband, Gov. Michael Dukakis, was
defeated in his 1988 presidential bid.
</TEXT>
