<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-Croce     07-15 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Croce,0121</SECOND>
<UNK>Publisher Joseph P. Croce Dead At 57</UNK>
<DATELINE>NORRISTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Joseph P. Croce, vice president of the
Intercounty Newspaper Group, which publishes 24 newspapers in
Pennsylvania and New Jersey, mostly weeklies, has died at age 57.
   Croce, who died Wednesday, was publisher of the group's Breeze
Newspapers, which Independent purchased in 1971. A cause of death
was not given.
   Among the eight newspapers under his wing, starting with north
Philadelphia's Tioga News in 1965, were the Northeast Advisor,
Bensalem Bulletin, the Conschohocken Recorder and the North Penn
Chat.
   He is survived by his wife, Catherine Croce; two sons, Joseph P.
Jr. and Mark S.; a daughter, Cynthia Dunn; a brother; a sister and
two grandsons.
</TEXT>
