<FIRST>r i PM-Mecca-Fire     07-15 0230</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Mecca-Fire,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Five Trampled to Death in Fire Panic at Mecca Camp</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JIDDAH, Saudi Arabia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a tent camp
housing Moslems making the annual pilgrimage to Mecca, and five
elderly Pakistanis were trampled to death in the ensuing panic,
officials said today.
   Thirty-four others were hurt during the blaze that burned 220
tents Friday in the camp in Mecca, a civil defense official said in
a statement distributed by the Saudi Press Agency.
   The camp was set up by the South Asian Pilgrims Association, a
Pakistani-based organization that arranges travel and accomodations
for Moslems making the pilgrimage to the sacred Moslem city.
   The fire was caused by a flare from a gas cooker being used by
one of the pilgrims, the statement said. The civil defense official
said five elderly Pakistanis were trampled on as the pilgrims fled
the camp.
   Fifteen of the injured remained hospitalized today and the others
were treated and released.
   Such accidents are frequent during the pilgrimage season to
Islam's holiest shrines at Mecca and Medina. About 2 million
pilgrims from 80 countries gather for the rituals every year.
   The civil defense statement made it clear that authorities did
not suspect sabotage at the camp.
   Two bombs exploded in Mecca on Monday at the height of the
pilgrimage season. A Pakistani pilgrim was killed and 16 were
wounded in the blasts.
</TEXT>
