<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SeaOrdeal     07-15 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Sea Ordeal,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Survives 21 Days Adrift At Sea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DARWIN, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former Vietnamese refugee survived 21
days at sea in an 18-foot-long fishing dinghy before being washed
ashore on an island in the Timor Sea, Australian Associated Press
reported Saturday.
   Thep Van Tran of Darwin was on a fishing trip when his motor
failed and he drifted from the Perron Islands, southwest of Darwin,
to the remote Timorese island of Soe, the news agency said.
   Tran, 37, was found Tuesday near the village of Kolbane, about
450 miles northwest of Darwin, AAP reported.
   Tran has been detained by officials on Soe, but no reason has
been given, AAP said.
   It said he had left Vietnam 10 years ago.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
