<HEAD>Cigarette Butt Sets Polluted River Afire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A peasant threw a cigarette butt into an
oil-polluted Ukrainian river and set it on fire Saturday, destroying
two bridges and burning himself, the official Soviet news agency
Tass reported.
   The Nuren River in the Zhitomir District had been contaminated by
an oil spill five days earlier, Tass said. About 105,000 gallons of
oil flowed into the river after a bulldozer split a pipeline near
the village of Malye Moshki.
   The stream blazed for five hours along a distance of several
miles, the news agency said.
