<FIRST>r a AM-People-TomJones     07-15 0307</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Tom Jones,0317</SECOND>
<HEAD>Singer Loses Paternity Suit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Singer Tom Jones lost a paternity suit filed by a
27-year-old woman who spent three nights with him at a Manhattan
hotel two years ago, her lawyer said Saturday.
   A Family Court judge ruled Friday that Jones fathered 1-year-old
Jonathan Jones Berkery, who was born to Katherine Berkery on June
27, 1988, said Raoul Felder, Ms. Berkery's attorney.
   Judge Judith B. Sheindlin of Manhattan Family Court ordered
Jones, 48, to pay a weekly sum of $200 to Ms. Berkery for the
maintenance of the child, Felder said.
   When the ruling was made, Ms. Berkery was crying, Felder said.
``The baby was in the court and she said to the baby, `Now, you have
a father.'''
   The judge set a court hearing for Sept. 5 to hear the lawyer's
request for a larger monthly sum for his client.
   A message left at the White Plains home of one of Jones' lawyers
was not immediately returned. There was no answer at the Manhattan
law office of another attorney representing the singer.
   Felder said the judge's ruling was based on his client's
testimony and a blood and tissue test that showed there was a 99.76
percent degree of probability that Jones was the boy's father.
   He noted that Jones, who has a British wife, ``never showed up in
court to explain or deny'' that the child was his.
   Attorneys for the Welsh singer charged Ms. Berkery was a
prostitute and lied about her background.
   Ms. Berkery, an unmarried former restaurant manager, met Jones on
Oct. 29, 1987, at a restaurant and the couple spent three nights at
the Ritz-Carlton Hotel, Felder said.
   Jones recently scored a hit single with a remake of Prince's
``Kiss.'' He is best known for his singles ``It's Not Unusual'' and
``She's a Lady.''
</TEXT>
