<FIRST>r i AM-Hussein-Israel     07-15 0204</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hussein-Israel,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jordan's King Condemns Israeli Peace Proposal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   King Hussein of Jordan on Saturday rejected the
Israeli peace plan for the occupied territories, saying it did not
represent the goals of Palestinians.
   The plan ``is obviously, as it is, totally unacceptable,''
Hussein said in an interview on Channel 4's ``World This Week''
program. ``It denies the Palestinians everything they aspire to
achieve.''
   ``I believe that Israel must be persuaded to review its position,
and it is the duty of Israel's friends the world over ... to save
Israel from Israel, and save all of us as a result,'' Hussein said.
   Under the plan, Palestinians in the occupied West Bank and Gaza
Strip would elect representatives to negotiate a peace settlement
with Israel.
   Earlier this month, Prime Minister Yitzhak Shamir of Israel
accepted several hard-line conditions set by his right-wing Likud
bloc, including an end to the 19-month uprising in the territories
before negotiations begin. Another condition is that Jews would be
allowed to continue settling in the occupied lands.
   The conditions angered the left-of-center Labor Party, which
shares power with Likud in a coalition government. Labor has said
the conditions virtually kill the proposal because they are
unacceptable to Palestinians.
</TEXT>
