<HEAD>With PM-Time</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: For Saturday PMs</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some of the major holdings of Paramount Communications
Inc., which has made a $12.2 billion offer to acquire Time Inc. The
list does not include Paramount's Associates Corp. financial
services subsidiary, which the company says it plans to sell.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>ENTERTAINMENT</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Paramount Pictures, movie production.
   Paramount Television, television production.
   Paramount Home Video, videocassette releases.
   Madison Square Garden.
   Madison Square Garden Network, cable television sports network.
   New York Knicks, professional basketball team.
   New York Rangers, professional hockey team.
   79 percent of TVX Broadcast Group, five independent television
stations (pending).
   Famous Players, Canadian movie theaters.
   Interests in:
   _USA Network, cable television.
   _Cinamerica, movie theaters.
   _Cinema International Corp., overseas movie theaters
   _CIC Video, home video releases.
   _International Advertising Sales, television barter advertising
sales.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>PUBLISHING</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Simon &amp; Schuster.
   Prentice Hall books.
   Pocket Books.
   Betty Crocker books.
   Webster's New World.
   Mobil Travel Guides
   Frommer travel guides.
   Baedeker travel guides.
   J.K. Lasser tax guides.
   Prentice Hall Tax &amp; Professional Services.
   Prentice Hall Business and Professional Publishing.
   Prentice Hall Professional Software.
   Woodhead-Faulkner international publishers
   Macdonald Childrens Books.
</TEXT>
